<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Jim Gray and Catharine van Ingen, <a href="http://research.microsoft.com/research/pubs/view.aspx?msr_tr_id=MSR-TR-2005-166" class="external text" title="http://research.microsoft.com/research/pubs/view.aspx?msr_tr_id=MSR-TR-2005-166" rel="nofollow">"Empirical Measurements of Disk Failure Rates and Error Rates"</a>, MSTR-2005-166, December 2005</li>
<li id="cite_note-schroeder-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-schroeder_14-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.usenix.org/events/fast07/tech/schroeder.html" class="external text" title="http://www.usenix.org/events/fast07/tech/schroeder.html" rel="nofollow">Disk Failures in the Real World: What Does an MTTF of 1,000,000 Hours Mean to You?</a> Bianca Schroeder and <a href="/wiki/Garth_A._Gibson" title="Garth A. Gibson">Garth A. Gibson</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-sundby-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-sundby_15-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.cbltech.com/articles/IDC-RAID-viewpoint.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cbltech.com/articles/IDC-RAID-viewpoint.html" rel="nofollow">What to do when the RAID Array fails</a> Nick Sundby</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vldb/Gray81.html" class="external text" title="http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vldb/Gray81.html" rel="nofollow">Jim Gray: The Transaction Concept: Virtues and Limitations</a> (Invited Paper) <a href="http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vldb/vldb81.html#Gray81" class="external text" title="http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vldb/vldb81.html#Gray81" rel="nofollow">VLDB 1981</a>: 144-154</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.snia.org/education/dictionary/w/" class="external text" title="http://www.snia.org/education/dictionary/w/" rel="nofollow">"Definition of write-back cache at SNIA dictionary"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.snia.org/education/dictionary/w/" class="external free" title="http://www.snia.org/education/dictionary/w/" rel="nofollow">http://www.snia.org/education/dictionary/w/</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Definition+of+write-back+cache+at+SNIA+dictionary&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.snia.org%2Feducation%2Fdictionary%2Fw%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:RAID"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?patentnumber=4092732" class="external text" title="http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?patentnumber=4092732" rel="nofollow">US4,092,732</a> <span class="PDFlink noprint" style="font-size:smaller;">(<a href="http://www.pat2pdf.org/pat2pdf/foo.pl?number=4092732" class="external text" title="http://www.pat2pdf.org/pat2pdf/foo.pl?number=4092732" rel="nofollow">PDF version</a>)</span> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1978-05-30"><a href="/wiki/1978" title="1978">1978</a>-<a href="/wiki/May_30" title="May 30">05-30</a></span>) Norman Ken Ouchi, <i>System for recovering data stored in failed memory unit</i>.<span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Apatent&amp;rft.number=4092732&amp;rft.cc=US&amp;rft.title=System+for+recovering+data+stored+in+failed+memory+unit&amp;rft.inventor=Norman+Ken+Ouchi&amp;rft.date=1978-05-30"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-patterson-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-patterson_19-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal"><a href="/wiki/David_A._Patterson_(scientist)" title="David A. Patterson (scientist)" class="mw-redirect">Patterson, David</a>; <a href="/wiki/Garth_A._Gibson" title="Garth A. Gibson">Gibson, Garth A.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Randy_Katz" title="Randy Katz">Katz, Randy</a> (1988). "<a href="http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Pubs/TechRpts/1987/CSD-87-391.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Pubs/TechRpts/1987/CSD-87-391.pdf" rel="nofollow">A Case for Redundant Arrays of Inexpensive Disks (RAID)</a>" (PDF). <i><a href="/wiki/SIGMOD" title="SIGMOD">SIGMOD</a> Conference</i>: pp 109–116. <span class="reference-accessdate">Retrieved on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-12-31"><a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a>-<a href="/wiki/December_31" title="December 31">12-31</a></span></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BSIGMOD%5D%5D+Conference&amp;rft.atitle=A+Case+for+Redundant+Arrays+of+Inexpensive+Disks+%28RAID%29&amp;rft.aulast=Patterson&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pages=pp+109%E2%80%93116&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eecs.berkeley.edu%2FPubs%2FTechRpts%2F1987%2FCSD-87-391.pdf"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
